UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Erman COIL, Appellee. No. 6622. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 12, 1931.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges, and JAMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of counsel for appellant, consented to by counsel for appellee, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
